The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing on March 12, 2013. The Press Secretary, Jay Carney, discussed various topics including gun violence, the budget, and the President's upcoming trip to the Middle East. Carney addressed concerns about the President's remarks being limited to a print pooler and not a broader pool. He also addressed the Senate Judiciary Committee's vote on gun control measures and the President's discussions with Senate Democrats. Carney discussed the Ryan budget and the President's view on balance. He also mentioned the President's commitment to engagement and finding common ground with lawmakers. Carney briefly mentioned the President's upcoming trip to the Middle East and his meetings with American Jewish and Arab American leaders. He also mentioned the President's commitment to diversity in his Cabinet. Carney did not have any information on the reported hack of personal information belonging to the First Lady and other officials.